accessibility.text: Does everyone feel the same feeling
No.  Sometimes certain harmonies can make most people feel something, but never everyone.
The beauty of music is that everyone can feel something different when they listen or play.

There are so many reasons why someone may feel something different than someone else while listening to music.  A person could not like a song that is supposed to be happy, or someone could find comfort in a song that usually makes people sad.
